# Compiled extension host + webview bundles live in `out/` (built by
# esbuild) and MUST be packaged — the extension's `main` entry is
# `./out/extension.js` and the editor webview loads `./out/webview.js` via
# `asWebviewUri`. The blanket `out/**` exclusion was an over-eager leftover
# from the bootstrap; intentionally NOT re-added here.

# Webview HTML + CSS are runtime assets read directly from disk by
# `AgentEditorPanel._renderHtml()` (see src/ui/agentEditorPanel.ts). They
# are NOT bundled — they ship as-is from `src/ui/webview/`. The negation
# patterns below are defensive: the only `src/**` exclusions above target
# test files and `__tests__/` directories, so these files are already
# included. The negations guard against a future maintainer adding a broad
# `src/**` rule that would silently break the webview at runtime.
!src/ui/webview/webview.html
!src/ui/webview/webview.css
